We know that on Windows 7 we need to tweak the windows registry like below to make Office Connector works (CONF-18174).

This is not scalable for customers with large number of dispersed users. 

We should create a tool to help make Confluence administrator's life easier by configuring the Registry automatically.

Steps to reproduce
# install confluence on Windows with {{confluence.home}} set to root directory. For example:
{noformat}
confluence.home=E:
{noformat}
# export a space to PDF, it will succeed
# try to download, we will get page not found. Because the url will be http://<confluenceURL>/download/emp/pdfexport-20110317-170311-1041-9/Home-170311-1041-10.pdf
(i) notice *emp* instead of *temp*.

In {{com.atlassian.confluence.importexport.DefaultImportExportManager#prepareDownloadPath}} we should remove trailing slash when we obtained String for homeDir because java.io.File does not remove it for Windows Root directory {{"E:\"}}:
{code}
    public String prepareDownloadPath(String path) throws IOException
     {
         String homeDir = new File(bootstrapManager.getConfluenceHome()).getCanonicalPath();   --> should be checked for trailing slash
{code}


h5. Work around
make sure that confluence.home is saved to a folder. Thus:
{noformat}
confluence.home=E:/data
{noformat}

