h3.Steps to replicate:

   1. Create a page with Layout Macros (\{section} and \{column}) and numbered or bulleted lists.
Example:
{code}
{section}
{column}
Column 1

* List item 1
* List item 2
* List item 3{column}
{column}
Column 2

* List item 1
* List item 2
* List item 3{column}{section} 
{code}
   2. Then switch to Rich Text editing and select one of the "list item" paragraphs.
   3. I apply a paragraph format with the scroll menu, for example "Panel".

h3.Problem:

Panel format is applied a much greater area than the one selected. The behavior depends on the surroundings, sometimes only all list items are formatted, sometimes the whole "column" block.

h3.Workaround:

The only way to apply the format to the selection is to manually add both block limits.

*NOTE:* The problem does NOT seem to occur with Headings, only with formats such as Panel, Code, Preformatted, Quote - and only within bulleted or numbered lists.

